1
00:00:02,166 --> 00:00:04,083
[music playing]

2
00:00:04,166 --> 00:00:05,125
[wood clatters]

3
00:00:05,208 --> 00:00:06,125
[Subaru yells]

4
00:00:06,208 --> 00:00:08,291
[grunting]

5
00:00:09,083 --> 00:00:11,666
<i>Everything</i>
<i>that we've both faced,</i>

6
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:14,333
<i>it all worked out</i>
<i>thanks to me, didn't it?!</i>

7
00:00:14,416 --> 00:00:16,791
<i>Without me there, things</i>
<i>would</i>
<i>have been a whole lot worse!</i>

8
00:00:16,875 --> 00:00:19,625
<i>You were saved</i>
<i>'cause I was there for you!</i>

9
00:00:19,708 --> 00:00:21,666
- [growls]
-<i> Don't you see?</i>

10
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:22,541
<i>You should have</i>
<i>a greater debt to me</i>

11
00:00:22,625 --> 00:00:25,208
<i>than you could ever repay!</i>

12
00:00:25,291 --> 00:00:27,333
[groans]

13
00:00:27,416 --> 00:00:30,041
[panting]

14
00:00:33,958 --> 00:00:36,250
- Perhaps we should pause
and take a little break
now.

15
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:41,250
<i>- Then I'll repay all of them</i>
<i>at this moment by ending this.</i>

16
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:42,916
[woman vocalizing]

17
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:49,125
FELIX:<i> I swear, Julius,</i>

18
00:00:49,208 --> 00:00:50,750
<i>your good nature</i>
<i>is going to waste</i>

19
00:00:50,833 --> 00:00:53,291
<i>playing the villain</i>
<i>for someone like him.</i>

20
00:00:53,375 --> 00:00:54,625
JULIUS:<i> Excuse me?</i>

21
00:00:54,708 --> 00:00:57,500
<i>I haven't the slightest idea</i>
<i>what you're talking about.</i>

22
00:00:57,583 --> 00:00:58,750
FELIX:<i> Why get yourself punished</i>

23
00:00:58,833 --> 00:01:01,291
<i>trying to protect</i>
<i>a guy like that? It's foolish.</i>

24
00:01:01,375 --> 00:01:04,291
<i>- I acted as I wished,</i>
<i>true to my nature,</i>

25
00:01:04,375 --> 00:01:08,708
<i>righteously, in my own way,</i>
<i>and without shame.</i>

26
00:01:08,791 --> 00:01:10,041
<i>Understand?</i>

27
00:01:11,416 --> 00:01:13,458
FELIX: Are you sure about this?

28
00:01:13,541 --> 00:01:16,750
After all, Old Man Wil
is busy preparing, too.

29
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:18,583
- It was a request
from our guest,

30
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:20,041
so I can't ignore it.

31
00:01:20,125 --> 00:01:22,500
- If they're just practicing,
it's neo big deal,

32
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:25,333
but honestly, it looks to me

33
00:01:25,416 --> 00:01:27,333
like he's
just making up excuses.

34
00:01:27,416 --> 00:01:29,208
- What do you mean?

35
00:01:29,291 --> 00:01:30,833
- He wants to be able to say,

36
00:01:30,916 --> 00:01:33,250
"I'm doing just fine now
and working hard," you
know?

37
00:01:34,666 --> 00:01:36,458
- Well, can you blame him?

38
00:01:38,375 --> 00:01:39,291
- Oh.

39
00:01:41,541 --> 00:01:44,833
[no audible dialogue]

40
00:01:44,916 --> 00:01:46,875
- [chanting]

41
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:55,500
- ♪ Now let me open the scar ♪

42
00:01:55,583 --> 00:01:59,208
♪<i> Tokeatta</i> virus ♪

43
00:01:59,291 --> 00:02:00,291
[singing in Japanese]

44
00:02:43,791 --> 00:02:46,458
♪ Now let me open the scar ♪

45
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:48,541
♪<i> Tokeatta</i> virus ♪

46
00:02:48,625 --> 00:02:50,666
[singing in Japanese]

47
00:02:53,583 --> 00:02:55,958
♪ Grew up in the loneliness ♪

48
00:02:56,041 --> 00:02:58,208
[singing in Japanese]

49
00:03:14,958 --> 00:03:16,791
- Forgive me.

50
00:03:16,875 --> 00:03:17,708
- Whoa, wait a second.

51
00:03:17,791 --> 00:03:18,875
There's no need for that.

52
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:21,583
What have you got
to apologize for?

53
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:22,416
None of this was your fault,

54
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:25,000
so don't try
to shoulder the blame.

55
00:03:25,083 --> 00:03:26,291
- No.
- [gasps]

56
00:03:26,375 --> 00:03:29,291
- I'm a friend to you
as well as to Julius.

57
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:32,416
I feel that my own
lack of virtue was responsible.

58
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:35,708
I failed to stop a dispute
between two friends.

59
00:03:35,791 --> 00:03:38,458
That duel,
there was no meaning behind it.

60
00:03:38,541 --> 00:03:39,666
- Wait. What?

61
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:41,791
There was no meaning?

62
00:03:41,875 --> 00:03:42,750
- Yes.

63
00:03:42,833 --> 00:03:45,833
As nothing of value came
from you two fighting.

64
00:03:45,916 --> 00:03:47,541
You were hurt,

65
00:03:47,625 --> 00:03:50,666
and Julius ended up tarnishing
his career as a knight.

66
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:54,958
Why not try to have a calm,
open discussion with him?

67
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:56,875
I'm sure that would clear up
any misundersta--

68
00:03:56,958 --> 00:03:58,916
- Look, Reinhard...
- [gasps]

69
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,750
- I get how you feel,
and I appreciate it, honestly.

70
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:04,916
- You really are a nice guy.
- So then--

71
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,625
- But I just can't accept
that proposal.

72
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:07,708
We're done talking.

73
00:04:07,791 --> 00:04:09,875
You should go back.

74
00:04:10,916 --> 00:04:12,375
- Subaru.

75
00:04:12,458 --> 00:04:13,833
Then tell me why?

76
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:15,833
What was it you gained
from that duel?

77
00:04:15,916 --> 00:04:17,625
You've only suffered
great losses.

78
00:04:17,708 --> 00:04:19,041
- [gate creaks]
- Even Miss Emilia--

79
00:04:19,125 --> 00:04:21,250
- You'd better head back
for today, Reinhard...

80
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:23,000
before your mistress
gets lonely

81
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:25,500
and starts yelling for you.

82
00:04:25,583 --> 00:04:27,000
- [gate clangs]
- [gasps]

83
00:04:30,916 --> 00:04:33,416
- Mind your own damn business.

84
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:38,500
[wood clattering]

85
00:04:38,583 --> 00:04:40,458
[yelps]

86
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:42,791
[panting]

87
00:04:42,875 --> 00:04:44,500
- Maybe we should stop
and call it a day.

88
00:04:44,583 --> 00:04:47,833
- [panting]

89
00:04:47,916 --> 00:04:48,583
[growls]

90
00:04:48,666 --> 00:04:50,708
- [wood clatters]
- [Subaru groans]

91
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:51,750
[thump]

92
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:54,833
[fountain gushing]

93
00:04:54,916 --> 00:04:57,708
- Hey there. You must be
tired after your practice.

94
00:04:57,791 --> 00:04:58,708
- [sighs]

95
00:04:58,791 --> 00:05:00,125
- [chuckles]

96
00:05:01,125 --> 00:05:03,583
- Let me ask you something, Rem.

97
00:05:03,666 --> 00:05:05,958
Do you think I'm pathetic?

98
00:05:06,041 --> 00:05:07,583
- Yes, I do.

99
00:05:07,666 --> 00:05:09,708
- You do? Seriously?

100
00:05:09,791 --> 00:05:12,583
Then why are you still here
with a loser like me?

101
00:05:12,666 --> 00:05:14,416
Is it because you were told to?

102
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,333
- The fact that I think
you're pathetic

103
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:19,541
and my staying with you
are not contradictory.

104
00:05:19,625 --> 00:05:21,083
And even if I
hadn't been ordered to,

105
00:05:21,166 --> 00:05:23,916
I'm certain I would have
stayed with you.

106
00:05:24,583 --> 00:05:25,625
- Why?

107
00:05:25,708 --> 00:05:28,000
- That's simple.

108
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:29,375
Because I want to.

109
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:32,958
What do you think?

110
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,458
Shall we go out tomorrow?

111
00:05:35,541 --> 00:05:36,833
You haven't gone anywhere

112
00:05:36,916 --> 00:05:38,666
in the three days
since we came here.

113
00:05:43,208 --> 00:05:45,333
[bell tolling]

114
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:52,041
- Interested
in the royal selection, too, eh?

115
00:05:52,125 --> 00:05:53,666
- Whoa! Easy.

116
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:54,791
Don't sneak up on me like that.

117
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:57,541
Uh, wait. Where's Rem?

118
00:05:57,625 --> 00:05:58,458
- [grunts]
- Eh?

119
00:06:01,083 --> 00:06:04,583
[sighs] Don't make someone with
no experience watch your shop.

120
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:07,583
- So we got five candidates?

121
00:06:07,666 --> 00:06:09,458
Well, it's nothing
short of insanity

122
00:06:09,541 --> 00:06:11,958
to let a half-elf be one of 'em,
if you ask me.

123
00:06:12,041 --> 00:06:13,250
"Emilia," huh?

124
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:16,500
There's no way
that a relative of the Witch

125
00:06:16,583 --> 00:06:17,833
could become our ruler.

126
00:06:17,916 --> 00:06:19,958
They gotta be crazy
to even consider it.

127
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:22,791
- Why does everybody say that?

128
00:06:22,875 --> 00:06:25,750
It doesn't mean she has
anything to do with the Witch.

129
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:28,250
- Huh?
- Uh, don't lump them together

130
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:30,125
and brush her off just because
she happens to be a half-elf!

131
00:06:30,208 --> 00:06:32,083
- [crowd murmuring]
- [gasps] Hey.

132
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:35,500
- Look, Emilia really cares.

133
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:37,250
Uh, I mean, that girl

134
00:06:37,333 --> 00:06:39,375
might really care about
this kingdom's people, too!

135
00:06:39,458 --> 00:06:41,916
- Why are you getting
so worked up about all of this?

136
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,000
- I'm not!
-<i> But it was for you,</i>

137
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:45,041
<i>now, wasn't it?</i>

138
00:06:45,125 --> 00:06:47,791
- [gasps]

139
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:48,416
Why is it?

140
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,208
Because of the Witch of Envy?

141
00:06:50,291 --> 00:06:52,625
That's the most ridiculous thing
I've ever heard!

142
00:06:52,708 --> 00:06:54,041
You think
all half-elves are dangerous

143
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:54,750
just because the Witch was one?!

144
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:57,083
- That's right.

145
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:59,208
You listen to me.

146
00:06:59,291 --> 00:07:01,500
Every citizen around here
is scared of the Witch.

147
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:02,833
That's just common knowledge.

148
00:07:02,916 --> 00:07:03,666
- [sputters]

149
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:06,125
- As long as people
see her like that,

150
00:07:06,208 --> 00:07:08,708
there isn't any chance
she's gonna win this.

151
00:07:08,791 --> 00:07:10,083
- [crowd murmuring]
- I know, right?

152
00:07:10,166 --> 00:07:14,041
- [scoffs] Who would actually
choose to support her, anyway?

153
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:16,958
- [gasps]

154
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:18,708
- Just a word of advice.

155
00:07:18,791 --> 00:07:21,833
Try not say the word "Witch"
too loudly in public.

156
00:07:21,916 --> 00:07:23,958
You never know who's listening
or where.

157
00:07:27,666 --> 00:07:28,625
- [grunts]

158
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:33,958
Emilia, you never told me...

159
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:37,041
everyone feels that way
about you.

160
00:07:37,125 --> 00:07:39,791
<i>- I can't understand</i>
<i>if you don't tell me, Subaru.</i>

161
00:07:39,875 --> 00:07:42,750
- You know what?

162
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:44,875
That goes both ways, Emilia.

163
00:07:44,958 --> 00:07:46,958
[music playing]

164
00:07:57,958 --> 00:08:00,291
[music playing only]

165
00:08:05,375 --> 00:08:06,250
[music ends]

166
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:08,125
[footsteps pattering]

167
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:11,833
Hmm?

168
00:08:11,916 --> 00:08:13,541
- Subaru Natsuki,

169
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:14,833
would you mind
joining me for a bit?

170
00:08:14,916 --> 00:08:17,041
- Miss Crusch, right?

171
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:19,250
- Yes, that's right.

172
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:21,583
Oh, of course.

173
00:08:21,666 --> 00:08:23,625
This is probably
the first time you've seen me

174
00:08:23,708 --> 00:08:25,750
out of my business attire,
isn't it?

175
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:27,708
The breeze
is pleasantly cool tonight,

176
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:29,083
perfect conditions
for sharing a drink

177
00:08:29,166 --> 00:08:32,791
as we gaze out
upon the night sky.

178
00:08:35,791 --> 00:08:38,083
- Uh, I'm too young
to drink alcohol.

179
00:08:38,166 --> 00:08:39,666
- You're welcome
to have some water, then.

180
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:43,291
Don't worry. I won't be
drinking
enough to get drunk tonight.

181
00:08:43,375 --> 00:08:45,333
[ice clinking]

182
00:08:49,791 --> 00:08:50,708
- [sighs]

183
00:08:54,916 --> 00:08:57,208
- Tell me,
how's the healing of your gate?

184
00:08:57,291 --> 00:08:58,875
- Huh?

185
00:08:58,958 --> 00:09:00,208
<i>- Neow, neow.</i>
<i>- Hey!</i>

186
00:09:00,291 --> 00:09:01,833
Oh. [chuckles]

187
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:05,291
I guess not too bad.

188
00:09:05,375 --> 00:09:06,166
- Hmm.

189
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:09,041
Well, Felix is excellent
with healing magic.

190
00:09:09,125 --> 00:09:10,958
You can put your trust in him.

191
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:16,125
- What about you?

192
00:09:16,208 --> 00:09:17,000
You seem to be
pretty busy lately.

193
00:09:17,083 --> 00:09:19,125
- Yes, indeed.

194
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:21,583
My family's currently
gathering people and supplies

195
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:22,500
in response
to a certain occurrence.

196
00:09:22,583 --> 00:09:26,541
Also, since word
of the royal selection spread,

197
00:09:26,625 --> 00:09:28,791
I've received proposals
every day now.

198
00:09:28,875 --> 00:09:30,583
I'm sure the other candidates
have as well.

199
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:32,791
- [spits]
Did you say, "Proposals"?

200
00:09:32,875 --> 00:09:34,958
You mean as in marriage?!

201
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:36,250
Oh, yeah.

202
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:38,208
I guess they're all single,
aren't they?

203
00:09:38,291 --> 00:09:38,958
- Does that bother you?

204
00:09:39,041 --> 00:09:41,666
- Uh, not really.

205
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:42,875
It's just--

206
00:09:42,958 --> 00:09:44,958
Oh, wait. That's right.

207
00:09:45,041 --> 00:09:46,250
I remember
Mr. Wilhelm telling me

208
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:48,083
that he had a beautiful wife.

209
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:51,291
- Are you aware of why
he's acting as my servant?

210
00:09:51,375 --> 00:09:53,000
Seems rather curious to me.

211
00:09:53,083 --> 00:09:56,041
- Huh? Why is that?

212
00:09:56,125 --> 00:09:57,458
- [squeal]

213
00:09:57,541 --> 00:10:00,333
What are you doing out here
with Miss Crusch, Subaru?!

214
00:10:00,416 --> 00:10:01,333
And, Miss Crusch,

215
00:10:01,416 --> 00:10:04,125
why are you dressed
so vulnerably?

216
00:10:04,208 --> 00:10:06,833
- Is it strange?
I mean, it's no different

217
00:10:06,916 --> 00:10:08,708
from what I wear
when I dine with you.

218
00:10:08,791 --> 00:10:09,750
- Well, yes, I know.

219
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:10,666
That's exactly the problem.

220
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:13,625
'Cause men are nothing
but wolves, Miss!

221
00:10:13,708 --> 00:10:14,458
- Don't forget.
You're a man, too.

222
00:10:14,541 --> 00:10:18,000
- That's enough joking around,
Felix.

223
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:20,791
Everyone who was present
at the royal selection

224
00:10:20,875 --> 00:10:23,166
knows whom Subaru
has real feelings for.

225
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:24,666
- Yeah, that's true.

226
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:26,041
I heard they had
a big fight, though.

227
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:27,833
- [grumbles]
- Aww!

228
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,208
Don't be mad, Subaru.

229
00:10:29,291 --> 00:10:31,375
You're so easy to read.

230
00:10:31,458 --> 00:10:32,166
- [sighs]

231
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:34,666
- Don't cast your gaze down,
Subaru.

232
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:36,875
- Huh?
- When your eyes are clouded,

233
00:10:36,958 --> 00:10:39,416
your soul darkens,
your future is closed,

234
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:42,375
and you lose sight
of your reasons to live.

235
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:45,375
When you do
what you know to be right,

236
00:10:45,458 --> 00:10:49,041
what is it you possibly hope
to achieve by looking downward.

237
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:52,750
Lift your head, face forward,
and reach out.

238
00:10:52,833 --> 00:10:53,583
It is not in my preferred stance

239
00:10:53,666 --> 00:10:57,208
to regard you
as an insignificant enemy.

240
00:10:57,291 --> 00:10:59,958
- If Miss Crusch says so,

241
00:11:00,041 --> 00:11:02,000
you have neo choice
in the matter.

242
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:03,708
The point is, Subaru,

243
00:11:03,791 --> 00:11:06,750
you need to hurry up
and make up with Miss Emilia.

244
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:09,416
So think about how
you accomplish that, and do it!

245
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:12,458
Seriously,
it's as simple as that.

246
00:11:13,541 --> 00:11:17,125
<i>- How I can accomplish that,</i>
<i>huh?</i>

247
00:11:22,375 --> 00:11:24,000
There is something,
and only I can do it.

248
00:11:24,083 --> 00:11:25,958
- Huh?
- Oh?

249
00:11:26,041 --> 00:11:27,500
[no audible dialogue]

250
00:11:27,583 --> 00:11:29,333
- [sighs]

251
00:11:29,416 --> 00:11:32,250
Yeah, I know
that's what needs to happen.

252
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:34,333
It's so clear to me now.

253
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:36,208
You don't even
have to tell me a thing.

254
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:40,083
- Hmm.
- [wind blowing]

255
00:11:41,166 --> 00:11:43,416
The wind is picking up.

256
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,833
From the looks of things,

257
00:11:45,916 --> 00:11:47,833
I'd say the weather
will be rough again tomorrow.

258
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:54,333
[wood clatters]

259
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:59,208
- What do you say, young man?
Shall we stop for now?

260
00:11:59,291 --> 00:12:00,291
- Come on. You kidding me?

261
00:12:00,375 --> 00:12:02,375
You've seen how far I've come

262
00:12:02,458 --> 00:12:04,375
taking blows
and rolling with it, right?

263
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:05,583
- Your attitude
seems quite different.

264
00:12:05,666 --> 00:12:08,333
I'm sensing a change in you
this morning.

265
00:12:08,416 --> 00:12:10,708
- It's possible,
'cause Miss Crusch

266
00:12:10,791 --> 00:12:12,791
gave me some much-needed advice
last night.

267
00:12:14,041 --> 00:12:14,791
<i>If I just get a chance,</i>

268
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:18,041
<i>I can make</i>
<i>any problem I have go away.</i>

269
00:12:18,125 --> 00:12:21,000
- Hmm. I see.

270
00:12:21,083 --> 00:12:23,416
I must suggest
that we call it a day.

271
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:24,416
- Eh?

272
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:25,500
- Well, in my opinion,

273
00:12:25,583 --> 00:12:27,416
it's become rather meaningless.

274
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:29,750
Why bother teaching someone

275
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:30,666
who's abandoned the option
to get stronger

276
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:33,125
how to use a sword
that makes him stronger?

277
00:12:33,208 --> 00:12:35,166
- Uh, hang on.

278
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:37,166
What do you mean by--

279
00:12:37,250 --> 00:12:38,291
- Subaru.
- Eh?

280
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:42,041
- We need to talk
about something.

281
00:12:45,250 --> 00:12:47,333
- Has Rem told you
what's been going on?

282
00:12:47,416 --> 00:12:50,833
- The feeling I sensed
was something like a presence

283
00:12:50,916 --> 00:12:53,291
through the sense
that I share with my sister.

284
00:12:53,375 --> 00:12:55,166
I wish she could have used
her clairvoyance

285
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:57,958
to get a clear picture,
but that's all I have.

286
00:12:58,041 --> 00:12:59,041
- So you must have picked up

287
00:12:59,125 --> 00:13:01,875
a nasty sort of synesthesia
from her, I take it?

288
00:13:01,958 --> 00:13:03,375
- We're not sure
of the details yet,

289
00:13:03,458 --> 00:13:06,000
but it's
from the Mathers domain,

290
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:08,833
which you know
as Margrave Roswaal's territory.

291
00:13:08,916 --> 00:13:10,375
It seems some troubling movement

292
00:13:10,458 --> 00:13:13,041
was seen in the vicinity
of his mansion.

293
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:14,208
Parts of the domain

294
00:13:14,291 --> 00:13:16,583
are already on high alert
as we speak

295
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:18,041
- Troubling movement?

296
00:13:18,125 --> 00:13:18,583
- Indeed.

297
00:13:18,666 --> 00:13:21,000
We foresaw this situation

298
00:13:21,083 --> 00:13:24,500
from the moment the margrave
declared his intention

299
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:27,291
to back Miss Emilia, a half-elf.

300
00:13:27,375 --> 00:13:31,041
- You mean all of this is
happening because of prejudice?

301
00:13:31,125 --> 00:13:33,958
- That is likely
a correct summation.

302
00:13:34,041 --> 00:13:34,875
- [sputters]

303
00:13:34,958 --> 00:13:36,541
<i>The moment I leave her,</i>

304
00:13:36,625 --> 00:13:37,916
<i>this starts happening?</i>

305
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:38,791
- [gasps]

306
00:13:38,875 --> 00:13:40,500
<i>- Everyone around her</i>
<i>is an enemy.</i>

307
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:43,666
<i>Only one person</i>
<i>can take her side...</i>

308
00:13:46,291 --> 00:13:48,291
<i>and that would be me.</i>

309
00:13:48,375 --> 00:13:49,625
Okay, then.

310
00:13:49,708 --> 00:13:52,666
We have to go there and
help settle things, right?

311
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:55,458
- You mustn't, Subaru.

312
00:13:55,541 --> 00:13:57,833
You have to obey
Miss Emilia's orders.

313
00:13:57,916 --> 00:13:59,208
She said that you
should focus on healing,

314
00:13:59,291 --> 00:14:01,916
and I agree with her.

315
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,000
Making sure you're healed
must take priority.

316
00:14:05,166 --> 00:14:07,916
- Rem, no one's
at Emilia's side.

317
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,083
You and I are the only ones
who can help her.

318
00:14:10,166 --> 00:14:11,250
- [gasps]

319
00:14:12,666 --> 00:14:14,166
- You heard what I said,
Miss Crusch.

320
00:14:14,250 --> 00:14:18,541
We're going back to the
mansion,
right back to where Emilia is.

321
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:20,833
'Til it's taken care of,
my healing will just have to--

322
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:23,583
- Subaru Natsuki,
if you leave at this time,

323
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:25,333
I'm left with no choice

324
00:14:25,416 --> 00:14:27,416
- but to make you my enemy.
- Uh...

325
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:30,583
- Perhaps I need to correct
one idea you have.

326
00:14:30,666 --> 00:14:32,958
I've only allowed you
to stay here as a guest

327
00:14:33,041 --> 00:14:36,291
and receive treatment
because I'm contracted to do so.

328
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:37,541
- Contracted?

329
00:14:37,625 --> 00:14:38,958
- Yes, that's right.

330
00:14:39,041 --> 00:14:40,625
Emilia and I made an agreement

331
00:14:40,708 --> 00:14:43,458
regarding your treatment
as well as your safety.

332
00:14:43,541 --> 00:14:46,125
However, if you
abandon that yourself,

333
00:14:46,208 --> 00:14:49,250
I am not obligated
to continue protecting you.

334
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:50,666
The moment
you leave this household,

335
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:52,125
that deal is broken,

336
00:14:52,208 --> 00:14:55,541
and Emilia and I will
not hesitate to become enemies.

337
00:14:55,625 --> 00:14:57,625
- I was wrong about you.

338
00:14:57,708 --> 00:15:00,083
I thought
that maybe, just maybe,

339
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:02,291
you and I
could actually get along.

340
00:15:02,375 --> 00:15:04,416
Your advice,
that was just a little joke

341
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:05,458
over some drinks, right?

342
00:15:05,541 --> 00:15:08,291
I was stupid
to take you seriously

343
00:15:08,375 --> 00:15:11,208
when you told me, an enemy,
to do what I could.

344
00:15:11,291 --> 00:15:11,958
You don't want me to leave,

345
00:15:12,041 --> 00:15:14,291
because getting Emilia
out of trouble

346
00:15:14,375 --> 00:15:15,875
would be bad for you,
wouldn't it?

347
00:15:15,958 --> 00:15:17,625
- I think you seem to have
gotten some things wrong.

348
00:15:17,708 --> 00:15:20,958
- Felix, enough.
- No, I will say it.

349
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:23,500
The mistake he's making
is a bit too grave.

350
00:15:23,583 --> 00:15:26,291
Even if you leave here
and rush to her side,

351
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:27,708
nothing will change.
It's a waste of time.

352
00:15:27,791 --> 00:15:31,208
After making a fool of yourself
at the castle

353
00:15:31,291 --> 00:15:34,500
and being clobbered by Julius,
you still don't realize that?

354
00:15:34,583 --> 00:15:35,541
You'll be much better off
staying with us

355
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:38,458
and finishing up your treatment.

356
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:41,375
- I've decided.

357
00:15:41,458 --> 00:15:43,333
I'm going back to Emilia.

358
00:15:43,416 --> 00:15:46,458
Thanks for taking care of me,
though it wasn't for long.

359
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:48,958
- A good man knows
how to take a warning.

360
00:15:49,041 --> 00:15:50,458
I guess that saying's not true.

361
00:15:50,541 --> 00:15:53,166
- It's because of your warning
that I've made up my mind.

362
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:55,750
Thanks for that.

363
00:15:57,750 --> 00:15:59,333
[ground dragons snorting]

364
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:00,416
Rem, how long
until we reach the mansion?

365
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:03,375
- About 2 1/2 days, I think.

366
00:16:03,458 --> 00:16:04,625
- Over two days?

367
00:16:04,708 --> 00:16:06,708
But it took less
than half a day to get here.

368
00:16:06,791 --> 00:16:08,166
- When we came here,

369
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,583
we used a road
that's covered in fog now.

370
00:16:09,666 --> 00:16:11,625
We'll have to use a detour.

371
00:16:11,708 --> 00:16:12,708
- Who cares about a little fog?

372
00:16:12,791 --> 00:16:16,208
- The fog is created
by the White Whale.

373
00:16:16,291 --> 00:16:19,375
If we encounter it,
we'd never get out alive.

374
00:16:21,166 --> 00:16:22,666
- [gasps]

375
00:16:26,291 --> 00:16:28,041
- Thank you
for lending us your carriage.

376
00:16:28,125 --> 00:16:30,250
It is very much appreciated.

377
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:31,625
In my master's stead,

378
00:16:31,708 --> 00:16:33,541
thank you for all the kindness
you've shown us during our
stay.

379
00:16:33,625 --> 00:16:37,541
- Please,
take care of yourselves.

380
00:16:37,625 --> 00:16:39,625
[carriages rattling]

381
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:44,208
- Are you getting
anything from Ram?

382
00:16:44,291 --> 00:16:45,875
- Not yet. To an extent,

383
00:16:45,958 --> 00:16:48,416
our shared sense is something
consciously controlled.

384
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,666
I could be wrong,

385
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,708
but I believe
what I felt this morning

386
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:54,625
was something that exceeded
my sister's control.

387
00:16:54,708 --> 00:16:55,958
- I see.

388
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:58,791
So Ram didn't even mean
to let us know about it.

389
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:04,041
Is she trying to keep us
from getting involved?

390
00:17:05,666 --> 00:17:07,208
But why?

391
00:17:07,291 --> 00:17:09,625
She needs me by her side.

392
00:17:09,708 --> 00:17:11,333
- [sighs]

393
00:17:11,416 --> 00:17:14,083
- I know I can save her.

394
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:16,750
Once I do,
I'm sure she'll understand.

395
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:18,000
She has to.

396
00:17:27,416 --> 00:17:29,166
[carriage rattling]

397
00:17:30,875 --> 00:17:32,750
[gasps]

398
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:34,458
Why are we stopping here?

399
00:17:34,541 --> 00:17:35,791
We have to hurry.

400
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:38,250
- I'm sorry, Subaru,
but the ground dragon

401
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:39,458
can't go any farther right now.

402
00:17:39,541 --> 00:17:42,041
- [sighs]

403
00:17:49,375 --> 00:17:50,833
I can't sleep.

404
00:17:50,916 --> 00:17:53,666
- [knock at the door]
- [gasps]

405
00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:56,750
- Subaru, are you awake?

406
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:57,791
- Yeah.

407
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:06,083
[soft music playing]

408
00:18:07,416 --> 00:18:08,375
- I can't sleep,

409
00:18:08,458 --> 00:18:10,500
so I hoped that we could talk.

410
00:18:10,583 --> 00:18:11,916
- Really?

411
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,791
You, too?

412
00:18:13,875 --> 00:18:15,583
Can't help that, I guess.

413
00:18:21,416 --> 00:18:23,666
You're pretty worried
about the mansion

414
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:26,500
after what you felt through
your shared sense, aren't you?

415
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,666
Hey, it'll be fine.

416
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:31,333
We're not the sort
of loveable kids

417
00:18:31,416 --> 00:18:33,708
who get our feelings hurt
so easily.

418
00:18:33,791 --> 00:18:36,166
We'll get right back there,
and I'll fix things.

419
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:42,375
- Yes. I've put my faith
in you, Subaru.

420
00:18:43,916 --> 00:18:44,833
- [sighs]

421
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:48,833
[gasps]

422
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:56,458
You okay, Rem?

423
00:18:56,541 --> 00:18:58,208
Is--Is something wrong?

424
00:18:58,291 --> 00:18:59,708
Why are you holding on to me?

425
00:19:00,708 --> 00:19:02,166
- Because I want to.

426
00:19:02,583 --> 00:19:05,250
[energy humming]

427
00:19:06,791 --> 00:19:09,375
- Hey, I--

428
00:19:09,458 --> 00:19:10,708
I know this feeling.

429
00:19:10,791 --> 00:19:14,625
- Because I'm healing your gate,
just as Felix did, Subaru.

430
00:19:14,708 --> 00:19:16,666
- Oh, right. Healing.

431
00:19:16,750 --> 00:19:17,625
That makes sense.

432
00:19:17,708 --> 00:19:19,375
Yeah, sure. Of course you are.

433
00:19:19,458 --> 00:19:21,666
[chuckles]

434
00:19:23,041 --> 00:19:24,583
Thanks, Rem...

435
00:19:24,666 --> 00:19:25,833
really.

436
00:19:27,375 --> 00:19:29,750
Emilia, she'll be...

437
00:19:29,833 --> 00:19:30,958
angry with me, won't she?

438
00:19:31,041 --> 00:19:36,166
- If you take the time
to properly face her

439
00:19:36,250 --> 00:19:38,833
and communicate
how you feel with words,

440
00:19:38,916 --> 00:19:41,666
I'm sure she'll understand.

441
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:44,583
You're a truly wonderful person,
after all.

442
00:19:44,666 --> 00:19:45,375
- Yeah?

443
00:19:45,458 --> 00:19:47,875
I am?

444
00:19:47,958 --> 00:19:50,833
[chuckles] I guess so, huh?

445
00:19:50,916 --> 00:19:55,500
Emilia is hopeless without me,

446
00:19:55,583 --> 00:19:56,708
because I...

447
00:19:56,791 --> 00:20:00,958
care about her so much.

448
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:11,333
- Maybe save a tiny bit
of that for me as well.

449
00:20:13,583 --> 00:20:16,291
Now don't go anywhere,
okay, Subaru?

450
00:20:16,375 --> 00:20:17,666
And sweet dreams.

451
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:22,375
- [sighs]

452
00:20:25,666 --> 00:20:26,791
Rem, wake up!

453
00:20:26,875 --> 00:20:29,041
We overslept, so--[gasps]

454
00:20:33,041 --> 00:20:33,625
- Well, now, good morning.

455
00:20:33,708 --> 00:20:35,500
How can I--

456
00:20:35,583 --> 00:20:36,958
- Have you seen
the blue-haired girl

457
00:20:37,041 --> 00:20:38,458
who checked in with me?!

458
00:20:38,541 --> 00:20:39,791
- The--The lady you were with--

459
00:20:39,875 --> 00:20:42,125
- Tell me where she is!

460
00:20:42,208 --> 00:20:44,875
- I was just gonna tell you
that she left during the
night.

461
00:20:44,958 --> 00:20:47,208
Here are the things
she left behind for you.

462
00:20:49,875 --> 00:20:51,708
- [gasps]

463
00:20:51,791 --> 00:20:53,833
- [gasps]
- What the hell?

464
00:20:53,916 --> 00:20:56,791
What are you thinking, Rem?

465
00:20:56,875 --> 00:20:59,708
I thought for sure
you would understand me.

466
00:20:59,791 --> 00:21:02,708
How could you do this?

467
00:21:07,041 --> 00:21:08,416
REM:<i> Dear Subaru,</i>

468
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:11,666
<i>I'll be gone by the time</i>
<i>you read this letter,</i>

469
00:21:11,750 --> 00:21:15,375
<i>and when you do, I'm sure</i>
<i>you'll be very angry with me.</i>

470
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:19,000
<i>I won't ask you to forgive me</i>

471
00:21:19,083 --> 00:21:21,500
<i>for leaving you behind</i>
<i>to go to the mansion.</i>

472
00:21:21,583 --> 00:21:22,916
- ...in there
might agree to your offer.

473
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,416
-<i> But please understand.</i>

474
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:28,583
<i>It would be very dangerous</i>
<i>to bring you there right now.</i>

475
00:21:28,666 --> 00:21:29,666
- Huh?

476
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:31,666
- Are you the one
who's named Otto?

477
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,750
- Uh...

478
00:21:33,833 --> 00:21:34,375
Okay, yes,
I'll accept your payment...

479
00:21:34,458 --> 00:21:36,416
-<i> So please just be patient</i>

480
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:38,791
<i>and wait here for me to return.</i>

481
00:21:38,875 --> 00:21:40,041
- [sighs]

482
00:21:43,625 --> 00:21:45,375
- So that's it, huh?

483
00:21:45,458 --> 00:21:48,500
You think I'm a useless
good-for-nothing, too, Rem?

484
00:21:49,625 --> 00:21:50,291
- Oh, man.

485
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:52,666
I think
I've just been introduced

486
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:53,708
to someone who could be
real trouble for me.

487
00:21:53,791 --> 00:21:56,375
- Fine. Whatever.

488
00:21:56,458 --> 00:22:00,750
But if you won't trust me,
then why should I depend on you?

489
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:02,750
- [shudders]

490
00:22:10,416 --> 00:22:13,375
- [ground dragon wails]
- [grunts]

491
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:16,833
- I'm sorry, but would it
be okay if we turn back
now?

492
00:22:16,916 --> 00:22:20,791
- What? After coming this far?

493
00:22:20,875 --> 00:22:21,583
- My ground dragon
is frightened.

494
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:23,541
- [snarling]

495
00:22:23,625 --> 00:22:24,583
- It knows by instinct

496
00:22:24,666 --> 00:22:27,500
that this place
is too dangerous to approach.

497
00:22:27,583 --> 00:22:29,625
- So where are we, anyway?

498
00:22:31,083 --> 00:22:33,625
- Looks like we're already
in the Mathers domain,

499
00:22:33,708 --> 00:22:35,833
right by a village
that's called Arlam.

500
00:22:35,916 --> 00:22:37,000
- Got it.

501
00:22:37,083 --> 00:22:39,416
- Wait! Please!
Don't go out there!

502
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:41,416
Let's just head back, okay?

503
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:43,958
- Think you've taken me
close enough, Otto.

504
00:22:44,041 --> 00:22:46,375
You're welcome to take the money
and all my stuff, okay?

505
00:22:46,458 --> 00:22:49,750
- I can't do that.
Please, Natsuki, rethink this.

506
00:22:49,833 --> 00:22:50,583
Come back!

507
00:22:50,666 --> 00:22:52,500
- [panting]

508
